The paper discusses the application of deep learning models, specifically the differentiable neural computer (DNC), to question answering tasks. This falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions improvements to the memory unit and architecture of the DNC, which relates to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the model on a specific task related to reading comprehension (CNN RC task), which falls under computer vision (cs.CV).
